<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca12e53b-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s911"><num value="911">§ 911.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Interior shall prescribe such rules and regulations as will be necessary to the carrying out of the provisions of sections 908 to 910 of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idca12e53c-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1910-06-25/ch406/s4">June 25, 1910, ch. 406, § 4</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/835">36 Stat. 835</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
